  "prompt": "What are the International Business Methods?",
  "response": "International business methods refer to various strategies and approaches companies use when conducting business across national borders. Here are the key international business methods:\n\n1. Exporting/Importing\n- Direct exports\n- Indirect exports\n- Cross-border trade\n- International trading\n\n2. Licensing and Franchising\n- Technology licensing\n- Brand licensing\n- Franchise agreements\n- Intellectual property agreements\n\n3. Strategic Alliances\n- Joint ventures\n- Strategic partnerships\n- Collaborative arrangements\n- Research and development partnerships\n\n4. Foreign Direct Investment (FDI)\n- Wholly-owned subsidiaries\n- Greenfield investments\n- Mergers and acquisitions\n- Equity investments\n\n5. Contract Manufacturing\n- Outsourcing production\n- Original Equipment Manufacturing (OEM)\n- Original Design Manufacturing (ODM)\n\n6. E-commerce and Digital Platforms\n- Online international sales\n- Digital marketplaces\n- Cross-border digital transactions\n\n7. International Consultancy\n- Providing professional services\n- Management consulting\n- Technical expertise sharing\n\n8. International Procurement\n- Global sourcing\n- Supplier diversification\n- International vendor management\n\n9. Global Supply Chain Management\n- International logistics\n- Integrated supply networks\n- Cross-border distribution\n\n10. International Marketing Strategies\n- Global branding\n- Localization\n- Cultural adaptation\n- Market entry strategies\n\nThese methods help businesses expand globally and manage international operations effectively.",
